a and Polly Stewart Revisit a Literary Thriller</a></strong><span class="post_attribute center"><span class="post_detail_date">January 19, 2024</span> by <a href="https://crimereads.com/author/pollystewart/">Polly Stewart</a></span></div></li><li><div class="post_circle_thumb"><a href="https://crimereads.com/the-best-psychological-thrillers-of-january-2024/"><img class="lazy" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lb-content-widgets/img/lazy-sq.png" data-src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2024/01/psychological-thrillers-feat-150x150.jpg" alt=""></a></div><div class="text-container"><strong class="title"><a href="https://crimereads.com/the-best-psychological-thrillers-of-january-2024/">The Best Psychological Thrillers of January</a></strong><span class="post_attribute center"><span class="post_detail_date">January 19, 2024</span> by <a href="https://crimereads.com/author/molly-odintz/">Molly Odintz</a></span></div></li><li><div class="post_circle_thumb"><a href="https://crimereads.com/tracy-clark-and-gregg-hurwitz-talk-genre-fiction-and-social-justice/"><img class="lazy" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lb-content-widgets/img/lazy-sq.png" data-src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2024/01/tracy-and-gregg-150x150.jpg" alt=""></a></div><div class="text-container"><strong class="title"><a href="https://crimereads.com/tracy-clark-and-gregg-hurwitz-talk-genre-fiction-and-social-justice/">Tracy Clark and Gregg Hurwitz Talk Genre Fiction and Social Justice</a></strong><span class="post_attribute center"><span class="post_detail_date">January 19, 2024</span> by <a href="https://crimereads.com/author/crimereads/">CrimeReads </a></span></div></li></ul></li>
